West Nile fever, Spain
----------------------
Information received on (and dated) 10 Sep 2010 from Dr Lucio Ignacio
Carbajo Goni, [Deputy Director-General, Health, Primary Industries,
Directorate General of Agricultural and Livestock Resources, Ministry
of Environment and Rural and Marine Affairs, Madrid, Spain]

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Start date: 26 Aug 2010
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 2 Sep 2010
Report date: 10 Sep 2010
Date submitted to OIE: 10 Sep 2010
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: West Nile virus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic), laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country
Related reports: immediate notification (10 Sep 2010); follow-up
report no. 1 (1 Oct 2010) [see below]

New outbreaks
Outbreak 1: Cadiz, [Andalusia]
Date of start of the outbreak: 26 Aug 2010
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Species: Equidae
Susceptible: 4
Cases: 1
Deaths: 0
Destroyed: 0
Slaughtered: 0

Outbreak 2: Cadiz, [Andalusia]
Date of start of the outbreak: 30 Aug 2010
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals
Species: Equidae
Susceptible: 3
Cases: 1
Deaths: 1
Destroyed: 0

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 2
Total animals affected
Species: Equidae
Susceptible: 7
Cases: 2
Deaths: 0
Destroyed: 0
Slaughtered: 0

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: vectors.

Control measures
Measures applied: control of arthropods; control of wildlife
reservoirs; no vaccination; treatment of affected animals
(anti-inflammatories, antibiotics)
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Central Veterinary Laboratory, Algete
(national laboratory)
Species: Equidae
Test: competitive ELISA (c-ELISA)
Test date: 2 Sep 2010
Result: positive

Species: Equidae
Test: IgM-capture ELISA
Test date: 10 Sep 2010
Result: positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

