West Nile fever, Spain
----------------------
Information received on (and dated) 1 Oct 2010 from Dr Lucio Ignacio
Carbajo Goni, [Deputy Director-General, Health, Primary Industries,
Directorate General of Agricultural and Livestock Resources, Ministry
of Environment and Rural and Marine Affairs, Madrid, Spain]

Summary
Report type: follow-up report no. 1
Start date: 26 Aug 2010
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 2 Sep 2010
Report date: 1 Oct 2010
Date submitted to OIE: 1 Oct 2010
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: West Nile virus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic), laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country
Related reports: immediate notification (10 Sep 2010); follow-up
report no. 1 (1 Oct 2010)

[There were 14 new outbreaks, all in Andalusia, which are summarized
below. For details see the original OIE WAHID report referenced above.

New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 14
Total animals affected
Species: Equidae
Susceptible: 179
Cases: 18
Deaths: 1
Destroyed: 0
Slaughtered: 0

Outbreak statistics
Species: Equidae
Apparent morbidity rate: 10.06 percent
Apparent mortality rate: 0.56 percent
Apparent case fatality rate: 5.56 percent
Proportion susceptible animals lost*: 0.56 percent
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction,
and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: vectors

Control measures
Measures applied: control of arthropods; no vaccination; treatment of
affected animals (symptomatic treatment: anti-inflammatories,
antibiotics)
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

